      "id": "P_WHEN_RST_RISES_ABOVE_THRESHOLD_IMMEDIATELY",
      "observable_contract": "When `rst` rises above threshold, immediately restore `vout` to the midscale value of 0 V. While `rst` remains high, ignore clock edges and hold the restored midscale value. When `rst` is low, each rising `clk` crossing decodes `d6..d0` as a 7-bit binary word and drives `vout` to the center of that code bin across a bipolar 1.8 V span from `-0.9 V` to `+0.9 V`. Hold the output between clock events.",
